<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1733,1919]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,350,1813,1839]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Description.</emphasis>
The original description of 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[678,840,1813,1839]" pageId="9" pageNumber="52" refString="Cook, E. F. (1956 a) A contribution toward a monograph of family Scatopsidae (Diptera). 3. The genus Rhexoza Enderlein. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 49, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1956" yearSuffix="a">
Cook (
<number box="[757,818,1813,1839]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" value="1956.0">1956</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
is fairly complete for most details to allow species identification. I add here drawings of the thorax, wing, segment 
<number box="[903,917,1853,1879]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" value="7.0">7</number>
and the terminalia. Cook’s (
<number box="[1249,1311,1853,1879]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" value="1956.0">1956</number>
a, 
<figureCitation box="[1336,1401,1853,1879]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[173,1423,196,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[173,1423,194,1966]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Male terminalia of Swammerdamellini genera. 1 – 3. Pararhexosa chelata (Cook), 1971. Male paratype (1, ventral; 2, lateral, 3, dorsal). 4 – 5. Rhexoza subnitens (Verrall). 6 – 7. Akorhexoza sp. 1 (4, ventral, 5, dorsal)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/179669/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
<number box="[1390,1401,1853,1879]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
G) drawing of the male terminalia is not totally accurate, due to misinterpretation of sclerite homology.
</paragraph>
